### HYMN XXV

#### A charm to be used when a young ox is first yoked

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_1902501">1</span></span>I yoke thee
with the mind of one unwearied still and first of all.  
  Be thou a bearer up the hill: run hither bearing up thy load.

